<subSubSection pageId="313" pageNumber="314" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="313.[151,1436,438,861]" pageId="313" pageNumber="314">
REMARKS: 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[266,511,654,681]" pageId="313" pageNumber="314" pagination="1" refId="ref368514" refString="Rondani, C. (1859 b) Dipterologiae italicae prodromus. Vol: III. Species italicae ordinis dipterorum in genera characteribus definita, ordinatim collectae, methodo analitica distinctae, et novis vel minus cognitis descriptis. Pars secunda: Muscidae, Siphoninae et (partim) Tachininae. A. Stocchi, Parmae [= Parma], 243 + [1] p., 1 pl." type="journal article" year="1859">Rondani (1859b: 127)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1859" box="[631,794,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Exorista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="313" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fugax">
<emphasis box="[631,794,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="313" pageNumber="314">Exorista fugax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from a single female: “ 
<emphasis box="[1055,1436,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="313" pageNumber="314">Semel exemplar foemineum inveni</emphasis>
[Once I found a female specimen]”. 
<bibRefCitation author="Herting, B." box="[598,819,691,717]" pageId="313" pageNumber="314" pagination="189 - 204" refId="ref353650" refString="Herting, B. (1969) Notes on European Tachinidae (Dipt.) described by Rondani (1856 - 1868). Memorie della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 48 (2), 189 - 204." type="journal article" year="1969">Herting (1969: 194)</bibRefCitation>
stated: “The Rondani collection contains three different species under this name. The only specimen that agrees with the description is a female of 
<taxonomicName authority="Meigen" authorityName="Meigen" box="[1219,1432,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Drino" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="313" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lota">
<emphasis box="[1219,1337,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="313" pageNumber="314">Drino lota</emphasis>
Meigen
</taxonomicName>
, and this is obviously the type”. Unfortunately, he did not label the specimen he considered as the “type”. There are 
<specimenCount box="[240,376,799,825]" pageId="313" pageNumber="314" type="female">two females</specimenCount>
in the MZUF without any label indicating their type status: we are unable to single out the one upon which Rondani based his description. We leave the recognition of the 
<typeStatus box="[1045,1143,835,861]" pageId="313" pageNumber="314">holotype</typeStatus>
to a future specialist.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
